# Decide the Grill-Master Balance Between Fast Loop and Engine

## Question

When a call runs a wayfinder grilling session, which layer is the grill-master? Option A: the fast voice LLM runs the grilling skill directly in its system prompt with tracker-writing tools — sub-second turns, but a second implementation of grilling to keep honest with the Claude-session version. Option B: the engine (pi session) drives and voice relays — one implementation, but 10s+ turn latency that kills phone conversation. Joel's stance is "balance": decide the concrete split — which turn types the fast loop owns, which get handed to the engine, what the latency budget is per turn type, how the skill prompt is shared or generated so the two grill-masters don't fork, and what the handoff mid-call looks like (fast loop grills, engine synthesizes and writes?). Real-call latency measurements from the restored dial tone should inform this, but the shape of the split can be grilled before they exist.
